      • denullify

        public static <T,S extends T> T denullify(T t,
                                          S sub,
                                          S... subs)
        Denullifies the given object by substituting it with the provided sub or subs.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of object
        S - type of substitutes. Must extend <T>
        Parameters:
        t - object
        sub - first substitute
        subs - array of substitutes
        Returns:
        the object t itself if not null, otherwise returns the first non-null substitute from subs. May return null if all substitutes are null.

      • getIfNotNull

        public static <T,R> R getIfNotNull(T t,
                                   java.util.function.Function<T,R> func)
        Shortens null object validation before doing an operation on the given object that returns a value.
        Note that this does not validate null sub-objects.
        Also note that the operation cannot return void. For this, use doIfNotNull(Object, Consumer).
        Avoid assigning the returned value to a primitive data type as this method may return null even if func returns a primitive data type.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the object t
        R - type of return value of func
        Parameters:
        t - object
        func - operation to be done on the object
        Returns:
        null if object is null, otherwise returns the result of the operation
